  "doc_id": "18889",
  "text": "A second VWS locus was mapped to human chromosome 1p34 [CITATION_1] and VWS was confirmed to be genetically heterogeneous by the demonstration that mutations in the transcription factor Grainyhead-like 3 (GRHL3) underlie VWS in a subset of IRF6-negative families [CITATION_2] . Transfection of GRHL3 mutation variants into zebrafish embryos abrogated periderm development via a dominantnegative effect, while all Grhl3-null mouse embryos developed abnormal periderm resulting in cleft palate in 17% of cases [CITATION_3] , confirming that VWS2 is also a peridermopathy. A common risk variant (rs41268753; p.Thr454Met) in the GRHL3 coding sequence is also an important contributor to nonsyndromic cleft palate [38, [CITATION_4] . Notably, this variant has been shown to disrupt periderm development in zebrafish [38] .",
